name: Asus TUF GAMING A520M-PLUS
description:
One of the most affordable microATX gaming motherboards of 2020 with an AMD AM4 processor socket based on the low-cost A520 chipset. It belongs to the models of the popular Asus The Ultimate Force line of gaming products, created for users who prefer a combination of reliability and reasonable cost. Guaranteed to support 4/6/8/12/16-core Ryzen 3000 processors (Matisse and Matisse Refresh cores, 7nm) and Ryzen 4000 APUs (Renoir core, 7nm) without additional BIOS microcode update.

The Asus TUF GAMING A520M-PLUS motherboard is a good choice for an affordable gaming or multi-purpose home PC configuration. Cope with the role of an inexpensive basis of the office system. Equipped with an 8-phase digital power subsystem with aluminium heatsinks and 4 slots for installing DDR4 DIMMs with an effective frequency of up to 4800 MHz. At the same time, the maximum amount of RAM can reach 128 GB, which, with a huge margin, is enough to solve any household and professional tasks. When using hybrid processors with integrated graphics (APUs), you can do without buying a separate discrete graphics card. For video output, there are D-Sub (1920x1200 at 60Hz), HDMI 2.1 (up to 4K at 60Hz) and DVI-D (1920x1200 at 60Hz) ports.

name: Asus TUF GAMING B550M-PLUS
description:
Functional and compact mid-range microATX motherboard based on the 2020 AMD B550 chipset. Equipped with an AMD AM4 processor socket, it is positioned as a mid-range model in the popular Asus The Ultimate Force series of products for gamers, designed for those who demand maximum reliability and durability at a reasonable price. Designed to create performant gaming configurations at a reasonable cost and versatile home PCs.

Supports installation of 3rd generation Ryzen 3/5/7/9 processors with Matisse/Matisse Refresh (7nm) cores. Asus TUF GAMING B550M-PLUS motherboard layout is carefully optimized and adapted for self-assembly. The board is equipped with a powerful 10-phase (8+2) Digi+ VRM digital power supply system with aluminium heatsinks. Supports moderate overclocking of CPU and RAM, adapted for long-term operation under multi-threaded multimedia, computing or gaming load. Thanks to four slots for DIMM modules, it allows you to install up to 128 GB of high-speed DDR4 RAM (4x32 GB, while the maximum clock speed is 4600 MHz), which is more than enough for any current and future games. Two M.2 SSD drives are provided (one with PCI-E 4.0 support). High-speed traffic processing is provided by the Realtek RTL8125B controller (up to 2.5 Gbps).

name: Asus TUF GAMING B450-PLUS II
description:
2021 full-length ATX gaming motherboard with AMD AM4 socket and AMD B450 midrange chipset. Positioned as a mid-range model in the popular Asus The Ultimate Force series of gaming products, designed for those who prefer maximum reliability and durability at a reasonable price. It supports an impressive amount of DDR4 RAM (up to 128 GB in 4x32 GB scheme), which is more than enough for home use, gaming and solving the vast majority of professional tasks.

Asus TUF GAMING B450-PLUS II motherboard fully supports 4/6/8/12/16-core Ryzen 2000/3000/5000 CPUs (Vermeer/Matisse cores — 7nm or Pinnacle Ridge 12nm) and hybrid APU Ryzen 2000/ 3000/4000/5000 (Raven Ridge/Pinnacle Ridge cores — 12nm, Cezanne/Renoir — 7nm). This board is a good choice for users looking for a solid foundation for a general purpose home computer or low cost workstation. Equipped with a powerful 10-phase processor power subsystem, which is cooled by aluminium radiators. Suitable for light overclocking experiments (without a significant increase in supply voltages). Network communications are provided by a Realtek L8200A GbE LAN controller. For high-speed NVMe SSDs, two M.2 ports (PCI-E Gen3 x4) are provided.

name: Asus ROG STRIX B550-F GAMING
description:
One of Asus' high-quality, full-sized motherboards for AMD Ryzen processors based on the top 2019 AMD X570 chipset. It is a full-size ATX board from the popular Asus Strix Republic Of Gamers series of overclocking models, whose products are famous for their increased reliability and improved overclocking potential. This model implements most of the features of the flagship ROG Strix X570 Gaming series, including support for the ultra-fast PCI-E Gen4.0 system bus for the latest gaming graphics cards and a fast M.2 SSD.

The Asus ROG STRIX B550-F GAMING motherboard is guaranteed to be compatible with 3rd generation Ryzen 3/5/7/9 processors with Matisse and Matisse Refresh cores. It is positioned as a product of the upper price category, designed to create premium overclocking and gaming configurations. Equipped with a heavy-duty 14-phase (12+2) Digi+ Power Control processor power subsystem with advanced heatsinks. This model will certainly interest enthusiasts who are used to getting maximum performance through the use of non-standard modes and manual tuning techniques for key system components. Supports the installation of an impressive amount of DDR4 RAM (up to 128 GB).

name: Asus PRIME H510M-A
description:
Inexpensive and compact microATX motherboard based on the 2021 Intel H410 core chipset. Designed to create multifunctional office and universal household PCs. It can become the basis of a low-cost gaming or multimedia entertainment system. It is positioned as a product of the base price category of 2021. Equipped with Intel LGA1200 socket, guaranteed to be compatible with all 2/4/6/8/10-core 10th and 11th generation Intel Core 9/i7/i5/i3/Pentium Gold/Celeron CPUs (Comet Lake and Rocket Lake , 14 nm).

The Asus PRIME H510M-A motherboard is equipped with a high-quality digital 8-phase (6+2) CPU VRM power supply subsystem, which is equipped with an aluminium heatsink for impeccably stable performance under long-term and intensive multi-threaded workloads. Based on this model, you can build an inexpensive home workstation for processing digital content (converting and correcting multi-megapixel photos, rendering photorealistic visualizations, processing high/ultra-high resolution video files). The GbE LAN adapter Intel I219-V provides fast processing of network traffic with low latency. The board is capable of working with two modules of DDR4 RAM with a total capacity of up to 64 GB. There is one full-speed M.2 port for connecting a fast NVMe SSD drive and four connectors for working with SATA3 devices.

name: Gigabyte B550 AORUS ELITE V2
description:
The second revision of the successful full-size ATX gaming motherboard based on the 2020 AMD B550 chipset. Just like its predecessor, it is equipped with an AMD AM4 processor socket and is positioned as a mid-range model. It is one of the most affordable mid-range motherboards from the famous Gigabyte AORUS family of overclocking products. Designed for use in compact gaming and overclocking systems at a reasonable cost.

Compatible with 4-, 6-, 8-, 12- and 16-core AMD Ryzen 3000/5000 (Matisse/Vermeer, 7nm) and Ryzen 4000 (Renoir, 7nm) APUs. Unlike the previous generation models based on the B450 chipset, there is support for the PCI-E Gen4 x16 system interface, which doubles the speed of texture loading in new models of gaming graphics cards and doubles the data transfer speed with high-speed NVMe SSDs.

The Gigabyte B550 AORUS ELITE V2 motherboard is equipped with a powerful 14-phase CPU VRM power supply subsystem, the margin of safety of which is enough for flawlessly stable operation of the system and bold overclocking experiments. Thanks to four DIMM slots, an impressive total amount of RAM is supported (up to 128 GB DDR4 at up to 4733 MHz). Equipped with M.2 SSD heatsink, supports 2.5GbE LAN network interface.

name: Gigabyte B450M S2H rev. 1.0
description:
Affordable and compact microATX motherboard with mid-range AMD B450 chipset for Zen and Zen2 microarchitecture processors. The manufacturer claims compatibility with first/second/third generation AMD Ryzen 3/5/7/9 CPUs (based on Summit Ridge/Pinnacle Ridge/Matisse microarchitectures), APUs with integrated Radeon Vega graphics (Raven Ridge/Picasso) and low-cost Athlon Zen CPUs (Raven Ridge).

Motherboard Gigabyte Gigabyte B450M S2H rev. 1.0 is designed to build inexpensive home and office PCs, can be used to create a low-cost workstation or entry-level gaming system. Equipped with a seven-phase (4 + 3) processor power subsystem, made of high-quality components. Despite the presence of only two connectors for installing RAM modules, it supports an impressive amount of up to 32 GB, which is enough to solve the vast majority of professional tasks. Can drive one high-speed M.2 Socket 3 NVMe SSD in PCI-E 3.0 4x mode (up to 32 Gb/s) and four traditional SATA3 devices. Equipped with a high-performance Realtek RTL8111G gigabit network controller, it is capable of outputting high-quality 8-channel sound. There are 12 USB ports for connecting peripherals.

name: Asus PRIME A320M-K
description:
Affordable microATX motherboard with AMD AM4 processor socket. Based on the low-cost AMD A320 chipset, compatible with AMD Ryzen/Ryzen Pro (1st and 2nd generation), A-series hybrid models (7th generation) and Athlon X4 (Bristol Ridge core). It is positioned as an inexpensive and easy solution for assembling entry-level and mid-level office and home systems for everyday tasks. Supports up to 2 DDR4-2133/2400/2666 RAM modules with a maximum total capacity of up to 32 GB.

The Asus PRIME A320M-K motherboard is equipped with one PCI-E x16 Gen3 slot for installing high-performance discrete video cards and can output an image from the video core built into the processor via HDMI and VGA D-sub ports. There are 4 SATA3 connectors for connecting conventional HDD/SSD drives. For high-speed NVMe SSD drives, there is a separate M.2 port (PCI-E Gen3 x4). Fast traffic exchange is provided by the Realtek RTL8111H gigabit network adapter, the Realtek ALC887 audio codec, which has an improved analogue path, is responsible for audio output. Supports up to 12 USB ports (6xUSB 3.1 Gen1 and 6xUSB 2.0).

name: Asus PRIME B660M-A D4
description:
A multifunctional micro-ATX motherboard from Asus, which is part of the PRIME line and belongs to the middle class by its nature. It is based on the Intel B660 chipset, equipped with an LGA 1700 socket and is ready to work with the latest 12th generation Intel Core/Pentium/Celeron multi-core processors. As with other boards in the PRIME series, the emphasis is on the quality of the materials used, the reliability of work and the possibility of in-depth customization.

In particular, an advanced cooling system with VRM and PCH radiators is used, as well as hybrid connectors for connecting coolers and proprietary Fan Xpert software with an advanced level of control and cooling settings. The element base of Asus PRIME B660M-K D4 is designed using high-quality MOSFETs, chokes and capacitors. Advanced UEFI mode with a concise graphical interface, many in-depth settings and a search system gives a free hand to those users who prefer to control and configure all the technical nuances on their own.

The internal layout includes four slots for installing RAM (maximum speed 5333 MHz), two M.2 slots with support for the high-speed PCI-E 4.0 interface, as well as four ports for installing SATA 3 drives and a PCI-E 16x slot for a graphics card. All this makes it an equally interesting option both for use in a work computer and for installation in a multimedia or gaming system.

name: Asus TUF GAMING B450M-PRO II
description:
Compact and balanced microATX gaming motherboard based on AMD B450 midrange chipset with AMD AM4 processor socket. Refers to 2020 model year products from the popular Asus The Ultimate Force gaming family, whose models are primarily distinguished by reasonable cost, high reliability and good functionality. The manufacturer is positioned as a product of the middle price category.

Can be the basis of a high performance gaming system, multi-purpose home PC or entry-level workstation. Compact overall dimensions (24.4x24.4 cm) allow it to be installed in relatively compact microATX-cases of the Mini Tower format. Despite the compact form factor, the Asus TUF GAMING B450M-PRO II motherboard is equipped with four slots for installing high-speed DDR4 modules with an effective frequency of up to 4400 MHz.

It supports work with an impressive amount of memory (up to 128 GB), which will be more than enough for any current and future games, as well as resource-intensive professional applications. DisplayPort 1.2 and HDMI 2.0b digital interface connectors make it possible to feed a video signal to the monitor from the Radeon Vega graphics core built into the processor. Two full-speed M.2 connectors support the installation of high-speed NVMe SSDs.

name: Asus ROG STRIX B450-F GAMING II
description:
The official sequel to the popular ROG Strix motherboard that Asus launched in 2018. Like its predecessor, this model belongs to the ATX format, is based on the mid-range B450 system logic and is designed to work in tandem with a mid-range AMD processor. In particular, it is friends with most Ryzen processors based on the Zen 2 and Zen 3 architecture, including both the younger Bristol Ridge generation chips and the near-top Ryzen 7 processors from the Matisse, Renoir and Vermeer lines.

The manufacturer is positioned as a model of the middle price category, designed for assembling gaming systems of medium and high levels. Like all members of the ROG Strix series, the board has extensive overclocking capabilities, which will be of interest to overclocking enthusiasts who want to get the most out of the processor, graphics card and RAM chips. The main board is a moderately powerful 12-phase power subsystem with additional cooling of the near-socket space, VRM zone and replaceable heatsinks for M.2 slots.

To install DDR4 modules, there are 4 slots with support for a clock frequency of 4400 MHz and a maximum capacity of 128 GB. Two M.2 ports are provided for installing high-speed NVMe SSDs. Ordinary SSD or HDD drives are connected to one of the 6 available SATA connectors. The Gigabit LAN controller Intel I211-AT is responsible for connecting to the network and processing traffic. Additional board bonuses include support for dual graphics cards in Crossfire mode, a USB 3.2 Gen 2 controller, and a SupremeFX S1220A audio path with surround sound and digital noise reduction microphone. Like most motherboards in the ROG Strix series, it features RGB lighting with Aura Sync connectivity.

name: Gigabyte B550M AORUS ELITE
description:
Compact and full-featured microATX gaming motherboard based on the 2020 AMD B550 chipset. Equipped with an AMD AM4 processor socket, it is positioned as a mid-range model. It is one of the most affordable boards of this class from the popular family of gaming and overclocking products Gigabyte AORUS. This model is suitable for use in compact gaming and overclocking systems. Compatible with 4/6/8/12/16-core AMD Ryzen 3000 (Matisse/Matisse Refresh, 7nm) and Ryzen 4000 (Renoir, 7nm) APUs.

Unlike the previous generation models (based on the B450 chipset), there is full support for the PCI-E Gen 4.0 system interface, which makes it possible to double the texture loading speed in progressive models of new video cards and speed up data exchange with high-speed NVMe SSDs. The Gigabyte B550M AORUS ELITE motherboard is equipped with an 8-phase power subsystem, the margin of safety of which is quite enough for perfectly stable operation of the system during long-term multi-threaded gaming or computing loads. Thanks to 4 slots for DDR4 DIMMs, an impressive maximum total amount of RAM (up to 128 GB) is supported, which is more than enough for gaming, as well as solving any household and professional tasks.

name: Gigabyte B450 AORUS Elite V2
description:
Balanced ATX motherboard based on B450 midrange chipset. It is one of the most affordable models of the 2021 Gigabyte AORUS gaming line, designed for enthusiasts who value maximum reliability and support for fine-tuning key system components for efficient and safe overclocking. AMD AM4 socket supports AMD Ryzen and AMD Athlon processors with Zen/Zen2/Zen3 microarchitecture. Guaranteed full compatibility with five different generations of 2/4/6/8/12/16-core AMD Ryzen 3/5/7/9 CPUs (Vermeer/Matisse/Pinnacle Ridge/Summit Ridge), APUs with Radeon Vega graphics (Picasso /Raven Ridge/Renoir) and available Athlon Zen (Raven Ridge) CPUs.

It is intended for creation of multi-purpose home and gamer systems of average/high level. Thanks to the 10-phase CPU power subsystem, it is able to provide flawlessly stable operation under conditions of prolonged gaming and multi-threaded computing loads, which allows us to recommend it for use in configurations of affordable entry-level workstations. Supports basic and advanced overclocking features. Allows you to install up to 128 GB of RAM (DDR4 scheme 4x32GB, up to 3600 MHz). Compatible with professional and gaming graphics cards (including powerful top models). Capable of handling two NVMe SSDs with six SATA3 drives.

name: Gigabyte Z490 AORUS MASTER
description:
Superbly equipped overclocking ATX motherboard based on the top 2020 Intel Z490 chipset. Equipped with LGA 1200 socket to support 2/4/6/8/10-core 10th generation Intel Core i9/i7/i5/i3/Pentium/Celeron processors with Comet Lake microarchitecture (14nm). The manufacturer is positioned as a product of the upper price category from the popular Gigabyte AORUS gaming line, created for enthusiasts who prefer maximum reliability and durability.

Designed for assembling top-end premium gaming configurations (including multiGPU systems using AMD 2-Way CrossFireX and Nvidia 2-Way SLI technology). The Gigabyte Z490 AORUS MASTER motherboard received a powerful 14-phase power subsystem, the capabilities of which will be in demand during overclocking experiments. Equipped with four slots for DDR4 DIMMs, supports up to 128 GB of RAM, which is more than enough for gaming, streaming, any household and professional tasks. The minimum delays in the network game will be provided by a high-speed 2.5GbE LAN adapter, a dual-band Wi-Fi 6 (802.11n/ac/a) wireless module is responsible for data transfer over the air. The audio subsystem is based on the top 8-channel Realtek ALC1220-VB codec, which works with the Hi-Fi DAC ESS ES9118EQ.

name: Asus TUF GAMING A520M-PLUS WIFI
description:
Miniature motherboard format micro-ATX, sharpened for PC assembly based on AMD Ryzen hardware platform socket and AM4 processor socket. Equipped with an entry-level AMD A520 and far from the most powerful 8-phase power subsystem, which is why its main scope will be mid-range gaming or work PCs. The best option would be to install it in a PC with a 6/8-core Ryzen 5/7 caliber processor (support for Ryzen 3000/4000/5000 series chips is declared), a serious, but not record-breaking supply of DDR4 RAM, a high-speed NVMe drive and a mid-range graphics card.

-For GeForce RTX 3060. Asus TUF GAMING A520M-PLUS WIFI is a member of the popular Asus The Ultimate Force gaming family, which in 2022 came out under the slogan "strength, stability, reliability". In this case, stability and reliability is manifested in the use of compacted textolite, reinforced slots, SafeSlot latches, additional cooling of power circuits, and the like. The Fan Xpert 2 utility included with the board will help organize high-quality and intelligent case cooling, which will be automatically adjusted depending on the level of heating of the components.

The equipment of the device includes 4 DIMM slots for DDR4 RAM with a maximum frequency of 4866 MHz. The maximum possible amount of RAM is 128 GB (4×32 GB with support for XMP technology). There are 4 classic SATA3 connectors for installing drives and one modern M.2 port for installing a fast and compact SSD drive. The Realtek network controller supports high-speed 2.5 Gigabit internet connection and comes with a Wi-Fi 6E wireless adapter out of the box. As befits a serious gaming board, connectors for water cooling systems and RGB strips with Asus Aura Sync backlighting are generously scattered along the entire perimeter.

name: Asus ROG STRIX B550-F GAMING WIFI II
description:
A high-end 2022 motherboard from Asus from the popular Asus Republic Of Gamers series for gamers. Unlike most of its relatives, it is equipped with a mid-range AMD B550 chipset (AM4 socket) and is designed for experienced gamers who clearly know why they came to the store and do not like to overpay for marketing. Designed to work with most AMD Ryzen processors released between 2017 and 2022 (Vermeer, Cezanne, Renoir, Matisse, Picasso, Summit Ridge, Raven Ridge, and Pinnacle Ridge families).

Despite belonging to the middle class, it implements most of the proprietary features of the flagship ROG Strix series. In particular, this is support for the PCIe 4.0 data bus, a powerful 14-phase processor power converter, DIGI + voltage stabilization modules, flawless cooling of critical areas, Aura Sync proprietary backlight control complex, OptiMem drive optimization technology, dual UEFI BIOS operation mode, etc.

d. The board firmware contains additional troubleshooting tools, as well as custom overclocking profiles that are saved even after flashing the board. Otherwise, the Asus ROG STRIX B550-F GAMING WIFI II gentleman's kit has two M.2 ports with additional cooling, 2 steel slots for video cards with the ability to work in Crossfire pair mode, 4 DDR4 RAM slots with a maximum clock speed of 5100 MHz, as well as numerous thermal sensors, connectors for LED strips and several free zones for a water pump. As a bonus, a wireless module with a built-in Wi-Fi 6 and Bluetooth 5.2 wireless receiver is already installed on board. And the SupremeFX sound system is equipped with a dual amplifier and supports multi-channel sound virtualization technology.

name: Asus TUF GAMING B660-PLUS WIFI D4
description:
A mid-range motherboard from the Asus TUF family, based on the Intel B660 chipset and designed to work in tandem with 12th generation Intel Core, Pentium and Celeron processors. In terms of its functionality, it has come close to the flagship motherboards of past generations. Asus TUF GAMING B660-PLUS WIFI D4 boasts an impressive number of ports and expansions thanks to the use of a full-format ATX PCB, which includes four slots for RAM, 3 M.2 connectors for installing high-precision NVMe drives, 6 connectors for additional case coolers.

And for communication with the outside world, the board is equipped with a 2.5-gigabit LAN controller from Intel and a dual-band Wi-Fi 6 (802.11ax) wireless module with Bluetooth 5.2 support. Plus, this board supports Intel Turbo Boost Max, XMP and OptiMem II technologies, and also allows you to use overclocking DDR4 RAM with a maximum frequency of 5333 MHz. Since the model is part of the Asus The Ultimate Force line, it was created using a high-quality element base with an emphasis on increased reliability and extended service life: high-temperature polymer electrolyte capacitors, LowRDS MOSFETs, silent case chokes, etc. And the existing 11-phase subsystem is perfect for overclocking a 6 or 8-core Core i7 processor.

name: Asus PRIME B450M-A II
description:
Affordable entry-level microATX motherboard with AM4 processor socket and AMD B450 chipset. It features a practical layout and modest overall dimensions (24.4x24.0 cm), which allows it to be installed in compact microATX cases. Ensures correct operation of AMD Ryzen 1000/2000/3000/5000 (Summit Ridge, Pinnacle Ridge, Matisse, Vermeer), Ryzen 2000/3000/4000 (Raven Ridge, Picasso, Renoir) APUs and Athlon (Raven Ridge) CPUs.

It is positioned as a product of the base price category in 2021, focused on use in home and office configurations of entry-level and mid-range. The Asus PRIME B450M-A II motherboard is equipped with a six-phase processor power subsystem, made on the basis of a high-quality element base. With four DIMM slots, it can accept up to 128 GB of high-frequency DDR4 RAM (up to 4400 MHz). To build a high-speed storage subsystem, an M.2 port (PCI-E Gen3 x4) and 6 standard SATA3 connectors are provided. Realtek RTL8111H high-speed network controller performs real-time processing of network traffic.

name: Asus TUF GAMING B450M-PLUS II
description:
Compact and affordable 2021 ATX gaming motherboard with AMD AM4 socket and mid-range AMD B450 chipset. Positioned as the entry-level model of Asus' popular family of gaming products, The Ultimate Force, aimed at users looking for increased reliability and durability at a reasonable cost. Asus TUF GAMING B450M-PLUS II motherboard fully supports 4/6/8/12/16-core Ryzen 2000/3000/5000 processors (Vermeer/Matisse cores — 7 nm or Pinnacle Ridge 12 nm) and Ryzen 2000 hybrid APUs/ 3000/4000/5000 with integrated AMD Radeon Vega graphics (Raven Ridge/Pinnacle Ridge — 12nm, Cezanne/Renoir — 7nm).

It supports a large amount of DDR4 RAM (up to 128 GB with a frequency of up to 4400 MHz) and such an array is quite enough for domestic use, gaming and the vast majority of professional resource-intensive tasks. Equipped with a reliable digital 6-phase power subsystem. Network communications are provided by a Realtek RTL8111H GbE LAN controller. For high-speed NVMe SSDs, one M.2 port (PCI-E Gen3 x4) is provided.

name: Asus TUF GAMING B550M-E WIFI
description:
Compact 2021 micro-ATX motherboard with AMD AM4 socket and AMD B550 midrange chipset. Designed to work in tandem with Ryzen 3000, 4000 and 5000 series processors (Matisse, Vermeer and Renoir generation). He is a member of the popular The Ultimate Force gaming line, which focuses on features and durability. In particular, it uses an improved component base (solid polymer electrolyte capacitors, ferrite chokes, low resistance MOSFET assemblies), which makes it an interesting choice for a mid-level workstation based on 16-thread Ryzen 7 caliber processors.

Unlike legacy TUF motherboards, this model supports the 4th generation high-speed PCI-E interface, enabling reactive SSDs with transfer rates from 5000MB/s to 7500MB/s. The layout of the connection slots allows you to install one massive graphics card, four DDR4 4800 RAM sticks, a pair of M.2 SSDs, or four SATA3 drives into the system. Asus TUF GAMING B550M-E WIFI is equipped with a Realtek 2.5 Gigabit LAN controller and Wi-Fi 6 (802.11 a/b/g/n/ac/ax) and Bluetooth v 5.2 wireless modules to handle heavy network traffic with ease. A gigabit LAN adapter from Realtek is responsible for the high data exchange rate and low latency in network battles. Plus, this model is equipped with a TPM connector for connecting encryption keys, a COM port and additional connectors for installing RGB and ARGB tapes.

name: Gigabyte B550 Gaming X V2
description:
An upgraded version of the popular 2020 Gigabyte B550 Gaming X ATX gaming motherboard with AM4 CPU socket and AMD B550 mid-range chipset. It features a reinforced CPU power subsystem (13 phases instead of 12 phases) and improved RAM overclocking capabilities up to 4733 MHz. It is positioned as a product of the middle price category from the popular Gigabyte GAMING family, the models of which are aimed at demanding gamers and low-cost-conscious enthusiasts.

It is focused on use as part of performant gaming and overclocking configurations of a reasonable cost. Supports 4/6/8/12/16-core Ryzen 3000/5000 CPUs (Vermeer/Matisse/Matisse Refresh cores, 7nm) and Ryzen 4000 hybrid APUs (Cezanne and Renoir core, 7nm). The Gigabyte B550 Gaming X motherboard supports the high-speed PCI-E Gen4 system interface, which allows you to double the data transfer speed with high-speed NVMe SSDs and speed up texture loading in gaming graphics cards. The power of the 13-phase digital power converter based on LowRDS mosfets is enough for bold but reasonable overclocking experiments. The board is equipped with four slots for DDR4 RAM modules and supports up to 128 GB (4x32 GB). For a high-speed storage subsystem, there are two M.2 ports (one PCI-E Gen4 x4).

name: Asus TUF GAMING B550-PLUS (WI-FI)
description:
A well-equipped 2020 full-size ATX gaming motherboard for AMD Ryzen processors based on the mid-range AMD B550 chipset. Refers to products of the Asus The Ultimate Force gaming series, which are subject to mandatory long-term factory stress testing. All models of the Asus TUF family of boards are distinguished by the use of an element base of increased reliability (polymer electrolyte capacitors, silent packaged ferrite chokes, low resistance DrMOS assemblies) and are able to provide reinforced concrete stability during many hours of gaming sessions.

A distinctive feature of the Asus TUF GAMING B550-PLUS (WI-FI) motherboard is a pair of built-in high-speed network controllers (2.5GbE LAN Realtek cable module and dual-band wireless Wi-Fi 6 802.11/n/ac/ax + Bluetooth 5.0). 4/6/8/12/16-core Ryzen 3/5/7/9 3000 processors (Matisse, Vermeer, 7nm) and Ryzen 4000 APUs (Renoir with integrated Vega graphics core, 7nm) are fully supported. Positioned as a product of the middle price category, designed to create gaming and overclocking configurations. For impeccable reliability, it is equipped with a digital reinforced 10-phase (8 + 2) processor power subsystem.

name: Asus TUF GAMING B650-PLUS
description:
Well-balanced and well-equipped ATX motherboard based on AMD B650 system logic. Part of Asus' 2022 The Ultimate Force product line, designed for gamers looking for maximum reliability and durability at a reasonable price. Like all representatives of the TUF series, it has undergone a long hour-long factory test, which guarantees stability during long hours of gaming sessions.

Unlike most of its counterparts in the series, this board belongs to a higher level and is designed to build advanced work and gaming systems with AMD Ryzen 7000 series processors, introduced in 2022. The device is based on the new AMD AM5 system logic, supports data transfer via the PCI-E 5.0 bus and is friendly with high-speed DDR5 6400 memory. against the backdrop of a fairly powerful gaming / work system with a 16-core processor, 128 GB of RAM, an RTX 3080 caliber graphics card and several fast SSDs.

The layout of the elements provides for the use of three high-speed M.2 SSDs with support for the NVMe protocol and 4 drives with a SATA3 connection. High-speed traffic processing is provided by the Realtek controller with a bandwidth of 2.5 Gbps. With HDMI 2.1 and DisplayPort 1.4 video ports. the device is capable of displaying an image from the Vega video core built into many Ryzen processors.

name: Asus ROG STRIX B550-A GAMING
description:
Full size AMD Ryzen gaming motherboard based on the 2020 AMD B550 chipset. It is a full-size ATX board from the popular Asus Republic Of Gamers family of overclocking models, whose products are known for their increased reliability and good overclocking potential. This model supports most of the features of the flagship ROG Strix X570 series, including support for the fast PCI-E Gen4 system bus for new discrete graphics cards and fast NVMe SSDs.

Asus ROG STRIX B550-A GAMING motherboard is guaranteed to be compatible with 4/6/8/12/16-core Ryzen 3000/5000 CPUs with Matisse/Vermeer cores (7nm) and Ryzen 4000 APUs (Renoir, 7nm). It is positioned as a model of the upper part of the middle price category, designed to assemble performant overclocker and gaming configurations. Equipped with a powerful 14-phase (12 + 2) processor power subsystem, thanks to which it will be of interest to economical overclocking enthusiasts.
